sentences: Donald Clarke (born 1940) is an American writer on music.
Clarke was born in 1940 and raised in Kenosha, Wisconsin, worked ten years in a car factory, and graduated from the University of Wisconsin–Madison.

He lived in England from 1973 to 1998 before moving to Austin, Texas for five years.

He moved to West Des Moines, Iowa in 2003, where he worked for a time on the music e-zines Blueswax and Folkwax.
He moved to Allentown, Pennsylvania in 2009, and in 2014 to Colorado Springs.
